  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Psalm 37:14-15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 37:14-15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The wicked have drawn out the sword, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — They are furnished with all sorts of arms, and are ready to give the deadly blow. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "To slay such as be of upright conversation — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Those against whom they have no quarrel, for any injury they have done them; but only for their integrity and righteousness, or because they are better than themselves, and will not comply with their wicked counsels and courses. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Their sword shall enter into their own heart — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "God will not only defend the upright from their mischievous designs, but will make those designs to fall upon their own heads. “I cannot but think,” says a writer quoted here by Dr. Dodd, “that David understood by these weapons, with which he has furnished the ungodly, their bitter and malicious invectives, their false and foul reproaches, &c. These were the arms, in the use of which, as he frequently complains, they were admirably well skilled.” Thus, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 57:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) speaking of wicked men, he says, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Whose teeth are spears and arrows, and their tongue a sharp sword. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And if so, then ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 37:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " “will mean that their intention will be frustrated; they shall not do the mischief they intended; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "their bows shall be broken — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And their invectives and calumnies shall recoil and do themselves hurt; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "their ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "sharp ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sword, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "their false and malicious tongues, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall pierce through their own soul. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And that this was the psalmist’s meaning, who can doubt, after reading ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 64:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the wicked doers are said to have ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whet their tongue like a sword, and to shoot out their arrows, even bitter words.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
